<article class="page content-item">
    <header>
        <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
</div>



    </header>
    <p>Ogden Publications, Inc. (collectively referred to in this Privacy Statement as "we," "us," or "Ogden Publications, Inc.") recognize the importance of protecting the privacy of all information provided by users of our websites, subscribers to our magazines, registrants for our events, recipients of our email newsletters and all of our customers. We created this policy with a fundamental respect for our users&rsquo; right to privacy and to guide our relationships with our users. This privacy statement discloses the privacy practices for all products and services owned by Ogden Publications, Inc. A current list of our publications, websites, and products can be found at <a href="http://www.ogdenpubs.com/" target="_blank">http://www.ogdenpubs.com/</a>.</p>
<h2>INFORMATION COLLECTION AND USE</h2>
<p>Ogden Publications, Inc. collects information from our website users, magazine subscribers, email subscribers and customers. Below, we will describe the type of information we collect and how we use it to provide better services to our customers.</p>
<h3>Website</h3>
<p>When you visit our website we may automatically collect non-personally identifiable information, such as online behavior and information about your computer, mobile or other device. The information collected may include, without limitation, the make, model, settings, specifications (e.g., CPU speed, connection speed, browser type, operating system, device identifier) and geographic location of you and/or your computer, mobile or other device, as well as date/time stamp, IP address, pages visited, time of visits, content viewed, ads viewed, the site(s), application(s), destination(s), and/or service(s) you arrived from, and other clickstream data. We use this information to monitor and improve our websites and Services.</p>
<p>This information is collected through a third party service, Google Analytics.</p>
<p>We also use SiteCore Experience Marketing to track online behavior and serve content specific to your website usage. None of the information they collect personally identifies you to us. This is done through the use of a cookie, you can find out more information about our cookie usage below.</p>
<h3>Magazine Subscription</h3>
<p>When you subscribe to one of our publications, we may ask you to provide your name, mailing address, email address, phone number and credit card or other payment information. This information is collected so that we can fulfill your subscription, send you invoices, and contact you about your subscription. Once you become a subscriber we may store your subscription information, including its start date, renewal date, pricing, publication, and any customer service contacts you may have with us.</p>
<h3>Store Purchase</h3>
<p>When you purchase products offered through one of our websites or publications, we may ask you to provide your name, mailing address, email address, phone number, and credit card or other payment information. We also keep a history of your purchases. We use this information to fulfill your purchase, to better assist you when you visit or contact us in the future, and improve our product offerings.</p>
<h3>Payment Information</h3>
<p>For our services that require payment (such as certain events, products and subscriptions), we also collect credit card information (such as account name, number, expiration date, and verification code), which is used for billing purposes only. We utilize a service, Cybersource, to assist with payment management. For more information on how they handle personal data please visit their <a href="https://www.cybersource.com/privacy/" target="_blank">privacy policy</a>.</p>
<h3>Online Registration</h3>
<p>Registration may be required to participate in certain website features, such as commenting. When you register, you may be asked for personal information such as your name, email address, and a user name and password that you select. We collect this information to identify who you are, to provide you with access to the service you requested, and communicate forgotten password notifications.</p>
<p>Note that all personal information sent or posted via your commenting appears on our site and becomes public information for which we are not responsible.</p>
<h3>Newsletter</h3>
<p>When you sign-up for our newsletters, we may ask you to provide your name, email address, demographic information, hobbies, and interests. We use this information to provide the requested services as well as provide relevant special offers. We use demographic information about our audience to improve our service, for marketing purposes and/or industry reporting purposes.</p>
<p>We use a third-party provider, WhatCounts, to deliver our email messages. We gather statistics around email opening and clicks using industry standard technologies to help us monitor and improve our newsletter. For more information, please see <a href="https://www.whatcounts.com/privacy-

policy/" target="_blank">WhatCounts privacy policy</a>.</p>
<p>You can opt-out of our email messages at any time by following the unsubscribe instructions located near the bottom of each message. If you have received an email in error, or would like to submit a complaint regarding an email message you received, please contact our <a href="http://www.ogdenpubs.com/customer-service.aspx" target="_blank">Customer Care Department</a> or call 800-678-5779.</p>
<h3>Promotions</h3>
<p>When you enter a contest, sweepstakes or giveaway (&ldquo;promotion&rdquo;) we may ask you to provide your name, mailing address, phone number, email address, demographic information, and interests. We use the information collected to administer your participation in the promotion and to notify the winners and award prizes. Name, city and state will also be listed on our promotion winner&rsquo;s page, this is necessary to comply with promotion laws.</p>
<p>We may offer promotions that are sponsored or co-sponsored or presented with identified third parties. The third parties will be identified on the promotion entry form. By participating in such promotions the information you voluntarily submit may be provided to both Ogden Publications, Inc. and the third parties identified on the form. Ogden Publications has no control over the third parties&rsquo; use of this information. Participation in these promotions is completely voluntary and the user therefore has a choice whether to disclose requested information.</p>
<h3>Surveys</h3>
<p>When you participate in a survey or poll we may ask you to provide your name, mailing address, phone number, email address, demographic information, and/or interests. We use this information for market research, audience analysis and to improve our Services. We use a third-party provider, Survey Monkey, to conduct our surveys and polls. For more information, please see <a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/mp/legal/privacy-policy/" target="_blank">Survey Monkey&rsquo;s privacy policy</a>.</p>
<p>We may also share survey information with advertisers and marketing partners in an aggregated, non-personally identifiable form. Personal information will only be provided to third parties after ensuring that depending on the circumstances you have either consented or not objected.</p>
<h3>Email this Article</h3>
<p>If you elect to use our referral service for informing a friend about our articles, sites and services, we may ask for the friend's name and email address. Ogden Publications, Inc. will store and use this information to send the friend an invitation. This information may also be used to provide the friend information about our company and related products and services. The friend may contact us as specified in the subsequent message to request that no further communications be sent.</p>
<h3>Communications with Us</h3>
<p>We have features where users can submit information to us (such as our comment/feedback forms). Letters to the editor and similar submissions may be made public. Requests for service, support or information may be forwarded as needed to best respond to a specific request. We may retain emails and other information sent to us for our internal administrative purposes, and to help us to serve customers better.</p>
<h3>Communications from Us</h3>
<p>In order to best serve our customers, we may send updates that contain important information about our sites and services. For example, we may send new members a welcome message, confirmations on purchases or verification of password and username for our password-protected sites. We may also communicate with a user to provide requested services and for account-related issues via email, phone or regular mail.</p>
<p>We offer our users the option to receive information about our company and related products, services and special deals. Users can choose not to receive these communications, as set forth in our Permission section below.</p>
<h2>COOKIES AND OTHER TRACKING TECHNOLOGY</h2>
<p>Our websites have features that automatically collect information from users, to deliver content specific to users' interests and to honor their preferences. This information assists us in creating sites that will serve the needs of our users.</p>
<p>We use "cookies," a piece of data stored on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. The use of cookies and pixels enable us to track and target the interests of our users to enhance the experience on our sites.</p>
<p>Further, beacons are used in email messages to measure the effectiveness of our messaging and how visitors use our website.</p>
<h3>Disabling Cookies</h3>
<p>You can set your browser to accept or reject most cookies, or to notify you when a cookie is set. This can be done by visiting the relevant support page for your browser.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.google.com/support/chrome/bin/answer.py?hl=en&amp;answer=95647" target="_blank">Chrome Cookie Settings</a></p>
<p><a href="http://support.mozilla.com/en-US/kb/Cookies" target="_blank">Firefox Cookie Settings</a></p>
<p><a href="http://support.microsoft.com/kb/196955" target="_blank">Internet Explorer Cookie Settings</a></p>
<p><a href="http://docs.info.apple.com/article.html?path=Safari/3.0/en/9277.html" target="_blank">Safari Cookie Settings</a></p>
<p>Alternatively, you can opt out of a third-party vendor's use of cookies for personalized advertising by visiting <a href="http://www.aboutads.info/" target="_blank">DAA opt-out page</a> and/or <a href="http://www.networkadvertising.org/choices/" target="_blank">NAI consumer opt-out page</a>.</p>
<h3>Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
<p>1.<strong>Necessary</strong> Cookies: These cookies are essential, as they enable you to move around the website and use its features, such as accessing logged in or secure areas. The website cannot function properly without them.</p>
<p>2.<strong>Statistics</strong>: These cookies help website owners to understand how visitors interact with websites by collecting and reporting information anonymously.</p>
<p>3.<strong>Marketing</strong> Cookies: Marketing cookies are used to track visitors across websites. The intention is to display content and promotions that are relevant and engaging for the individual user and thereby more valuable for publishers and third party advertisers.</p>
